<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>

<worksheet xml:id="ic1-reading" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>IC-1 Reading</title>
    <objectives>
    <ul>
      <li><p>Things you should understand and know:
        <ul>
            <li>Recognize where a function of two variables is integrable over a rectangular region or a general region</li>
            <li>Recognize properties of double integrals</li>
            <li>Recognize when changing the order of integration may be needed</li>
        </ul></p>
        <p>Things you should be able to do:
        <ul>
            <li>Use properties to evaluate double integrals</li>
            <li>Evaluate a double integral over a rectangular or general region by writing it as an iterated integral</li>
            <li>Use double integrals to calculate areas, volumes, and average values</li>
            <li>Simplify the calculation of an iterated integral by changing the order of integration</li>
            <li>Calculate the volume of a region between two surfaces</li>
            <li>Solve problems involving double improper integrals</li>
        </ul></p>
      </li>
      <li><p>You will be assessed on the following criteria:
        <ul>
          <li><p>Problem structure: Solution should be organized and easy to follow, with clear, complete steps 
              that follow progressively from one to the next.</p></li>
          <li><p>Double Integrals over Rectangular Regions: Compute double integrals over rectangular regions. Compute 
            the volumes of solids using double integrals. Solve applied problems using double integrals over rectangular regions.</p></li>
          <li><p>Double Integrals over General Regions: Compute double integrals over general regions. Sketch regions 
            and write a double integral of a continuous function over the region. Calculate volumes of regions using 
            double integrals. Solve applied problems using double integrals over general regions.</p></li>
        </ul></p>
      </li>
    </ul>
    </objectives>
        <p>All of the readings for this course come from the OpenStax Calculus 
            Volume 3 textbook, which is available for free online at 
            <url href="https://openstax.org/details/books/calculus-volume-3">
                https://openstax.org/details/books/calculus-volume-3</url>. You 
                can read the textbook online or download a PDF version. 
                The textbook is also available in print from various retailers 
                if you prefer a physical copy.</p> 
        <p>For this lesson, you should read sections <url href="https://openstax.org/books/calculus-volume-3/pages/5-1-double-integrals-over-rectangular-regions">
            5.1 Double Integrals over Rectangular Regions</url>, and <url href="https://openstax.org/books/calculus-volume-3/pages/5-2-double-integrals-over-general-regions">
            5.2 Double Integrals over General Regions</url>. You should read through the sections carefully, 
            making sure to understand the definitions, examples, and key ideas. 
            You should also work through the exercises at the end of each section 
            to test your understanding and practice applying the concepts. Some of the 
            exercises at the end of the section are assigned in the WP assignments.</p>      
</worksheet>
